### Summary

While removing a project, Geo leaves `+deleted` folder behind on secondaries. This happens because `GitlabShellWorker` that is responsible for deleting this folder is inside a [run_after_commit` callback](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/blob/master/app/services/repositories/destroy_service.rb#L17-19) since we don't perform any database operation this callback will never be triggered.

### Steps to reproduce

1. Enable the feature flag: `Feature.enable(:geo_project_registry_ssot_sync)`;
1. Enable the selective sync on the group level;
1. Wait for the replication to finish;
1. Disable the selective sync;
1. Wait a few minutes;
1. Check the background pages on the Geo secondary node;

### Screenshots

![Screenshot_2020-06-18_20.32.59](/uploads/329cdd49115b3d08e0e34335ed24680c/Screenshot_2020-06-18_20.32.59.png)

### Possible fixes

Schedule the repository deletion to remove the +deleted folder after we trash the repositories in [EE::Projects::DestroyService#geo_replicate method](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/blob/master/ee/app/services/ee/projects/destroy_service.rb#L45-56).

### Problem to solve

This issue comes from [comment](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/merge_requests/31550#note_345475454)

For the following query

```graphql
query{
  project(fullPath: "craigmsmith/craigmsmith-railsgoat-example") {
    pipelines(status: SUCCESS, ref: "master"){
      nodes{
        securityReportSummary{
          dast{
            vulnerabilitiesCount
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

The DAST artifact will be queried in the DB then the artifact opened and parsed N+1 times, where N is number number of Pipelines.

#222374 is planning to use this query so it needs to be optimized.

### Implementation Strategy

One possible implementation strategy would be, after each security build runs, count the number of vulnerabilities and store that number on `Security::Scan` in the same way `scanned_resources_count` is.

That way, `securityReportSummary` would no longer need to parse the artifacts to count the vulnerabilities and could select all the counts in one SQL statement based on the Pipeline.

- [ ] Update DB to store vulnerabilities count on job completion
- [ ] Update `securityReportSummary` to get the counts from `Security::Scan`

